</p>
<p>Let's break that down: the <code>POST_SET_DATA</code> is a constant for an event called
<code>form.post_set_data</code>. This is called after the data behind the form is added to it:
in other words, after the <code>GenusScientist</code> is bound to each embedded form.</p>
<p>When that happens, the form system will call an <code>onPostSetData()</code> function, which we
are about to create: <code>public function onPostSetData()</code>. This will receive a <code>FormEvent</code>
object:</p>
