</p>
<p>This <code>$form</code> variable is a <code>Form</code> object, but you can treat it like an array, including
unsetting fields.</p>
<p>That's it for the form! The last step is to conditionally render the <code>user</code> field.
Because if we refresh right now, the form system yells at us:</p>
<blockquote><p>There's no <code>user</code> field inside of our template at line 9.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Wrap that in an if statement: <code>if genusScientistForm.user is defined</code>, then print it:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="a1f36a3a13">
    <div class="meta">
        <div class="actions">
            <span class="fa fa-clipboard js-activate-clipboard" data-toggle="tooltip" title="Copy Code" data-placement="top"></span>
        </div>
